---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const subprocessors = [
	{ name: 'Hetzner', purpose: 'Application hosting & compute', location: 'Germany / Finland (EU)' },
	{ name: 'Cloudflare', purpose: 'CDN, DNS, and edge delivery', location: 'Global edge (config in EU)' },
	{ name: 'Auth0 / Okta', purpose: 'Authentication / login', location: 'EU region' },
];
---
<PageLayout
	title="Privacy"
	activePath="/privacy"
	lede="How MetaProc handles your data. Short version: analyses run in throwaway, EU-hosted containers, sign-in is handled by Auth0, and you should never upload identifiable patient-level data."
	description="MetaProc privacy: ephemeral EU-hosted analysis containers, Auth0 sign-in, no identifiable patient-level data, and the list of sub-processors."
>
	<p slot="banner" class="mp-banner mp-banner--info">
		Last updated 14 June 2026. We may refine this policy as the service evolves; any
		material change will be noted here.
	</p>

	<h2>No identifiable patient-level data</h2>
	<p>
		MetaProc is a tool for <strong>aggregate, study-level meta-analysis</strong>: the
		summary statistics already published in papers (event counts, means, SDs, effect
		sizes). It is <strong>not</strong> designed for and you should <strong>not</strong>
		upload individual patient data or any directly identifiable personal information.
		Please remove identifiers before importing anything.
	</p>

	<h2>Ephemeral by design</h2>
	<p>
		Your analysis runs inside an <strong>isolated, RAM-backed container</strong> that is
		<strong>destroyed at the end of your session</strong>. Data you upload lives in that
		container's memory for the duration of your work and is not written to long-term
		storage by the analysis runtime. When your session ends, the container (and the data
		in it) is torn down. Projects you choose to save are downloaded to <strong>your own
		device</strong> as a <code>.rds</code> file — they are not stored on our servers.
	</p>

	<h2>Your account &amp; login</h2>
	<p>
		To use the hosted app you sign in through <strong>Auth0</strong>, our authentication
		provider. To manage your sign-in, Auth0 stores your <strong>email address and a login
		identity</strong>. This is the one piece of data MetaProc keeps about you that
		persists between sessions; it is used only to authenticate you and to control access,
		and is held in the EU. We do not sell it or use it for advertising.
	</p>

	<h2>Hosting &amp; sub-processors</h2>
	<p>
		MetaProc is hosted in the EU. The following sub-processors may handle data in the
		course of running the service:
	</p>
	<table>
		<thead>
			<tr><th>Sub-processor</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Location</th></tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			{subprocessors.map((s) => (
				<tr><td>{s.name}</td><td>{s.purpose}</td><td>{s.location}</td></tr>
			))}
		</tbody>
	</table>

	<h2>Erasure &amp; contact</h2>
	<p>
		Your uploaded analysis data is ephemeral and is gone when your session ends. Your
		<strong>login account</strong> (email and identity, held by Auth0) persists until you
		ask us to remove it. To delete your account and its associated login data, or for any
		privacy question or concern, contact
		<a href="mailto:myron.moskalyk@gmail.com?subject=metaproc%20privacy">myron.moskalyk@gmail.com</a>.
	</p>
</PageLayout>
